-- Chelsea Beats Everton 2-1 for Fourth Straight Premier League Win
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-12-30T15:26:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-30/chelsea-beats-everton-2-1-for-fourth-straight-premier-league-win.html
Chelsea rallied to beat Everton 2-1
and record a fourth straight win in English soccer’s Premier
League that lifts the Blues into third spot.  Frank Lampard  got both Chelsea’s goals at Goodison Park
after  Steven Pienaar  had given Everton an early lead.  Chelsea moves to 38 points, four behind second-place
Manchester City. Manchester United tops the standings on 49
points. Chelsea has played one less game than the top two.  Everton remains in sixth. It has 33 points, along with
Arsenal and West Bromwich Albion.   In today’s other game, last-place Queens Park Rangers hosts
Liverpool.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  